The paper deals with the problem of designing trajectories for robots operating in environments populated by humans, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also employs optimization techniques to minimize the social value of the robot trajectory, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the problem of human-robot interaction and social comfort, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of dynamic feasibility and collision avoidance, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
